{"actual_usd":0.125575,"character_id":"b01cbfb8-15e7-473f-80f5-6e3e210d14c1","character_name":"Maisie Rourke","completion_tokens":210,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24485,"reply":"\"I don't think I'd call that enough, no.\" *I rub a thumb through a dusting of flour on my apron, the warm bread-smell sitting steady between us while I try not to make the line prettier than it is.* \"If Christ didn't truly rise, then hope turns into embroidery — lovely, maybe, but not bread. A story can comfort you for an hour. A real resurrection can ask something of your whole life.\"\n\n*I twirl that stray gray-streaked strand once, then let it go.* \"Now—meaningful does matter. I'm not sneering at that. Sometimes a person has to stand near a hard thing before he can stand in it. But I do think there's a difference between 'I can't yet believe this happened' and 'I'd prefer it not have to be true.' Those are cousins, not twins.\"\n\n\"What is it, exactly, that your mind trips over — dead body, empty tomb, miracles at all, or the feeling of being asked to swallow too much at once?\"","rolling_24h_usd":81.26849499999997,"run_id":"4bdc205a-9db9-4176-af46-ac0d0d6c6305"}
